      "content": "it's weird how people treat it like a choice when the math seems to point so clearly in one direction. if the science says we need massive amounts of reliable carbon-free power right now, isn't focusing on the \"risks\" basically just a way to delay the inevitable? feels like the debate is sometimes used to ignore what the actual data requires.",
